"n. 格言，警句 【英】 n.格言,警句(pithy, compact saying) n. 格言, 箴言(简洁、机智、有教导性的话) 【记】1)apo远离, thegm = them他们－因为近墨者黑(格言)2)a一个, pot小瓶子－说的话能装进小瓶子(简练)－警句 【记】the 神+ gram 语→神的词语→圣人的话就是格言 【相关】a.o.m的几个全是格言：aphorism，axiom 几个以a开头，以m结尾都是格言 apothegm (n.)  ""pithy saying,"" 1550s, from Greek apophthegma ""terse, pointed saying,"" literally ""something clearly spoken,"" from apophthengesthai ""to speak one's opinion plainly,"" from apo- ""from"" (see apo-) + phthengesthai ""to utter."" See aphorism for nuances of usage. Spelling apophthegm, restored by Johnson, is preferred in England, according to OED."
